---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Restaurant Review Management Toronto | Toronto Restaurant Growth"
  description="Restaurant review management in Toronto. Get more 5-star reviews, respond to every review professionally, and turn your reputation into your best marketing channel. The GTA's only restaurant review specialist."
>

  <main style="padding-top: 80px;">

    <!-- HERO -->
    <section style="background: #1a1a1a; color: #f5f5f0; padding: 80px 0;">
      <div style="max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 40px 24px; text-align: center;">
        <h1 style="font-family: 'DM Serif Display', Georgia, serif; font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 2.8rem); margin-bottom: 20px; color: #fff;">
          Restaurant Review Management Toronto
        </h1>
        <p style="font-size: 1.25rem; color: #ccc; max-width: 640px; margin: 0 auto 32px;">
          Your reviews are your reputation. We build systems that generate more 5-star reviews, respond to every review professionally, and turn your online reputation into your most powerful marketing channel.
        </p>
        <a href="/contact/" style="display: inline-block; background: #E85D04; color: #fff; padding: 16px 32px; text-decoration: none; font-weight: 600; font-size: 1.1rem; border-radius: 6px;">
          Book a Free Google Audit
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- THE NUMBERS -->
    <section style="background: #fff; padding: 80px 0;">
      <div style="max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 24px;">
        <h2 style="font-family: 'DM Serif Display', Georgia, serif; font-size: clamp(1.6rem, 3vw, 2rem); margin-bottom: 24px; text-align: center;">
          Why Reviews Matter More Than Anything Else
        </h2>
        <p style="text-align: center; max-width: 600px; margin: 0 auto 16px; color: #4a4a4a;">
          Before someone visits your restaurant, they check your reviews. Every single time. Here's what the data shows.
        </p>

        <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); gap: 24px; margin: 32px 0;">
          <div style="text-align: center; padding: 24px; background: rgba(232,93,4,0.08); border-radius: 8px;">
            <div style="font-family: 'DM Serif Display', Georgia, serif; font-size: 2.4rem; color: #E85D04; font-weight: 700;">93%</div>
            <div style="font-size: 0.9rem; color: #4a4a4a; margin-top: 8px;">of diners read online reviews before choosing a restaurant</div>
          </div>
          <div style="text-align: center; padding: 24px; background: rgba(232,93,4,0.08); border-radius: 8px;">
            <div style="font-family: 'DM Serif Display', Georgia, serif; font-size: 2.4rem; color: #E85D04; font-weight: 700;">4.2</div>
            <div style="font-size: 0.9rem; color: #4a4a4a; margin-top: 8px;">minimum star rating before most people will consider visiting</div>
          </div>
          <div style="text-align: center; padding: 24px; background: rgba(232,93,4,0.08); border-radius: 8px;">
            <div style="font-family: 'DM Serif Display', Georgia, serif; font-size: 2.4rem; color: #E85D04; font-weight: 700;">53%</div>
            <div style="font-size: 0.9rem; color: #4a4a4a; margin-top: 8px;">of customers won't visit a business with less than 4 stars</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <p style="color: #4a4a4a; margin-bottom: 16px;">
          Reviews aren't just social proof. They're a direct ranking factor for Google Maps. Restaurants with more reviews, higher ratings, and recent review activity rank higher in local search. Your reviews are simultaneously your best marketing and your best SEO.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- THE PROBLEM -->
    <section style="background: #f5f5f0; padding: 80px 0;">
      <div style="max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 24px;">
        <h2 style="font-family: 'DM Serif Display', Georgia, serif; font-size: clamp(1.6rem, 3vw, 2rem); margin-bottom: 24px;">
          Your Reviews Are Working Against You
        </h2>
        <p style="color: #4a4a4a; margin-bottom: 16px;">
          You've poured everything into your restaurant — the menu, the ambiance, the service. But online, your reputation tells a different story. Here's what we see with most restaurants that come to us.
        </p>

        <h3 style="font-family: 'DM Serif Display', Georgia, serif; font-size: 1.4rem; margin: 24px 0 12px;">Bad reviews are sitting unanswered</h3>
        <p style="color: #4a4a4a; margin-bottom: 16px;">
          You got a 1-star review three months ago from someone who waited too long for their food. It's still sitting there with no response. Every potential customer who reads it sees a restaurant that doesn't care. Studies show that 45% of consumers are more likely to visit a business that responds to negative reviews. Your silence is louder than the complaint.
        </p>

        <h3 style="font-family: 'DM Serif Display', Georgia, serif; font-size: 1.4rem; margin: 24px 0 12px;">You have no system to generate good reviews</h3>
        <p style="color: #4a4a4a; margin-bottom: 16px;">
          Your happiest customers leave your restaurant thinking "that was amazing" and then... nothing. They don't leave a review because nobody asked them to. The only people motivated enough to leave reviews on their own are the ones who had a bad experience. Without a proactive review generation system, your online reputation will always lag behind the actual quality of your restaurant.
        </p>

        <h3 style="font-family: 'DM Serif Display', Georgia, serif; font-size: 1.4rem; margin: 24px 0 12px;">Your review count is stagnant</h3>
        <p style="color: #4a4a4a; margin-bottom: 16px;">
          You have 47 Google reviews. Your competitor across the street has 340. Even if your average rating is higher, Google sees their review velocity and volume as a stronger trust signal. They rank higher. They get more visibility. They get more customers. And those customers leave more reviews, creating a flywheel effect that pushes you further behind every month.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- WHAT WE DO -->
    <section style="background: #fff; padding: 80px 0;">
      <div style="max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 24px;">
        <h2 style="font-family: 'DM Serif Display', Georgia, serif; font-size: clamp(1.6rem, 3vw, 2rem); margin-bottom: 24px;">What You Get</h2>
        <p style="color: #4a4a4a; margin-bottom: 16px;">
          We build a complete review management ecosystem for your restaurant. Not just monitoring — active systems that generate reviews, respond professionally, and protect your reputation.
        </p>

        <h3 style="font-family: 'DM Serif Display', Georgia, serif; font-size: 1.4rem; margin: 24px 0 12px;">Review Response System</h3>
        <p style="color: #4a4a4a; margin-bottom: 16px;">
          Every review on Google, Yelp, and TripAdvisor gets a professional, personalized response within 24 hours. Not generic copy-paste templates — actual thoughtful responses that address the specific feedback.
        </p>
        <ul style="margin: 16px 0 24px 20px; color: #4a4a4a;">
          <li style="margin-bottom: 10px;"><strong>Positive review responses</strong> — We thank reviewers by name, reference specific details from their visit, and invite them back.</li>
          <li style="margin-bottom: 10px;"><strong>Negative review responses</strong> — We acknowledge the concern, apologize appropriately, offer to make it right, and move the conversation offline.</li>
          <li style="margin-bottom: 10px;"><strong>Fake review flagging</strong> — We monitor for fake reviews, competitor sabotage, and policy-violating content and file removal requests.</li>
        </ul>

        <div style="background: #f9f9f6; border-left: 3px solid #E85D04; padding: 20px; margin: 20px 0; border-radius: 4px; font-style: italic; color: #4a4a4a;">
          <p><strong>Example negative review response:</strong> "Hi Sarah, thank you for sharing your experience. I'm sorry the wait time didn't meet the standard we hold ourselves to — that's not the experience we want anyone to have at [Restaurant]. I'd love the chance to make it right. Could you reach out to me directly at [email]? We'd like to invite you back on us. — [Owner Name]"</p>
        </div>

        <h3 style="font-family: 'DM Serif Display', Georgia, serif; font-size: 1.4rem; margin: 24px 0 12px;">Review Generation System</h3>
        <p style="color: #4a4a4a; margin-bottom: 16px;">
          The most important part of review management isn't responding to reviews — it's generating new ones. We implement multiple touchpoints that make it effortless for happy customers to leave a review.
        </p>
        <ul style="margin: 16px 0 24px 20px; color: #4a4a4a;">
          <li style="margin-bottom: 10px;"><strong>Table-side QR codes</strong> — Custom-branded QR code cards placed on every table that link directly to your Google review page. One scan, one tap, done.</li>
          <li style="margin-bottom: 10px;"><strong>Automated follow-up texts</strong> — Automated text messages sent 2 hours after the dining experience. Our follow-up messages achieve a 15-22% review conversion rate.</li>
          <li style="margin-bottom: 10px;"><strong>Staff training program</strong> — We train your servers and hosts on when, how, and whom to ask for reviews.</li>
          <li style="margin-bottom: 10px;"><strong>Receipt and bill insert prompts</strong> — A subtle review prompt printed on receipts or included as a card with the bill.</li>
          <li style="margin-bottom: 10px;"><strong>Post-event and catering follow-up</strong> — For restaurants that host events or do catering, we create follow-up sequences specifically for these high-satisfaction moments.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 style="font-family: 'DM Serif Display', Georgia, serif; font-size: 1.4rem; margin: 24px 0 12px;">Reputation Monitoring</h3>
        <p style="color: #4a4a4a; margin-bottom: 16px;">
          We don't just monitor Google. We monitor every platform where your restaurant might be reviewed — Google, Yelp, TripAdvisor, Instagram, Facebook, and halal-specific platforms like Zabihah.com for halal restaurants.
        </p>

        <h3 style="font-family: 'DM Serif Display', Georgia, serif; font-size: 1.4rem; margin: 24px 0 12px;">Crisis Response Protocol</h3>
        <p style="color: #4a4a4a; margin-bottom: 16px;">
          Every restaurant will eventually face a review crisis. We have a protocol ready before it happens — rapid response within 2 hours for crisis-level reviews, social media monitoring, and a documented escalation playbook.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- HOW IT WORKS -->
    <section style="background: #f5f5f0; padding: 80px 0;">
      <div style="max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 24px;">
        <h2 style="font-family: 'DM Serif Display', Georgia, serif; font-size: clamp(1.6rem, 3vw, 2rem); margin-bottom: 24px;">How It Works</h2>

        <div style="margin-bottom: 32px;">
          <p><span style="display: inline-block; background: #E85D04; color: #fff; width: 36px; height: 36px; border-radius: 50%; text-align: center; line-height: 36px; font-weight: 700; margin-right: 12px;">1</span><strong>Audit</strong></p>
          <p style="color: #4a4a4a; margin-top: 8px;">We analyze your current review landscape across every platform: total review count, average rating, review velocity, response rate, sentiment patterns, and competitor benchmarks.</p>
        </div>

        <div style="margin-bottom: 32px;">
          <p><span style="display: inline-block; background: #E85D04; color: #fff; width: 36px; height: 36px; border-radius: 50%; text-align: center; line-height: 36px; font-weight: 700; margin-right: 12px;">2</span><strong>Plan</strong></p>
          <p style="color: #4a4a4a; margin-top: 8px;">We design a custom review management strategy based on your restaurant's specific situation. You approve everything before we implement a single thing.</p>
        </div>

        <div style="margin-bottom: 32px;">
          <p><span style="display: inline-block; background: #E85D04; color: #fff; width: 36px; height: 36px; border-radius: 50%; text-align: center; line-height: 36px; font-weight: 700; margin-right: 12px;">3</span><strong>Execute</strong></p>
          <p style="color: #4a4a4a; margin-top: 8px;">We install the review generation systems, begin monitoring and responding to every review within 24 hours, train your staff, and deploy QR codes and follow-up sequences. Most restaurants see a 300–500% increase in monthly review volume within the first 60 days.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- CASE STUDY -->
    <section style="background: #1a1a1a; color: #f5f5f0; padding: 80px 0;">
      <div style="max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 24px;">
        <h2 style="font-family: 'DM Serif Display', Georgia, serif; font-size: clamp(1.6rem, 3vw, 2rem); color: #fff; margin-bottom: 24px;">Real Results</h2>

        <div style="background: #1a1a1a; border-left: 4px solid #E85D04; padding: 32px; border-radius: 8px; margin: 24px 0; border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.1);">
          <p style="font-family: 'DM Serif Display', Georgia, serif; font-size: 2rem; color: #E85D04; font-weight: 700;">47 reviews to 280+ in 6 months</p>
          <p style="color: #ccc;">Crab Boil had 47 Google reviews with a 4.1-star average when they came to us. We implemented table-side QR codes, automated follow-up texts, and staff training. Within 6 months, their review count grew to over 280, their average rating climbed to 4.5 stars, and their Google Maps ranking jumped from position 8 to position 2 for "seafood restaurant Toronto."</p>
          <p style="margin-top: 16px;"><a href="/case-studies/crab-boil/" style="color: #E85D04; text-decoration: underline;">Read the full Crab Boil case study</a></p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- FAQ -->
    <section style="background: #f5f5f0; padding: 80px 0;">
      <div style="max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 24px;">
        <h2 style="font-family: 'DM Serif Display', Georgia, serif; font-size: clamp(1.6rem, 3vw, 2rem); margin-bottom: 24px;">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

        <div style="border-bottom: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 24px 0;">
          <h3 style="font-family: 'DM Serif Display', Georgia, serif; font-size: 1.15rem; margin-bottom: 10px; color: #1a1a1a;">How much does restaurant review management cost in Toronto?</h3>
          <p style="color: #4a4a4a;">Our review management packages start at $800/month for monitoring and professional response across Google, Yelp, and TripAdvisor. Full-service packages that include review generation systems, crisis response protocols, and monthly reporting range from $1,500–$2,500/month. Every engagement starts with a free review audit.</p>
        </div>

        <div style="border-bottom: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 24px 0;">
          <h3 style="font-family: 'DM Serif Display', Georgia, serif; font-size: 1.15rem; margin-bottom: 10px; color: #1a1a1a;">Can you remove bad reviews from Google?</h3>
          <p style="color: #4a4a4a;">No one can remove legitimate reviews from Google — anyone who tells you otherwise is lying. What we can do is flag reviews that violate Google's policies for removal. More importantly, our strategy focuses on generating enough genuine positive reviews that negative ones become statistically insignificant.</p>
        </div>

        <div style="border-bottom: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 24px 0;">
          <h3 style="font-family: 'DM Serif Display', Georgia, serif; font-size: 1.15rem; margin-bottom: 10px; color: #1a1a1a;">How do you get more reviews for my restaurant?</h3>
          <p style="color: #4a4a4a;">We implement a multi-touch review generation system: table-side QR codes, automated follow-up texts sent 2 hours after dining, trained staff who know when and how to ask, and receipt prompts. Most restaurants see a 300–500% increase in monthly review volume within the first 60 days.</p>
        </div>

        <div style="border-bottom: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 24px 0;">
          <h3 style="font-family: 'DM Serif Display', Georgia, serif; font-size: 1.15rem; margin-bottom: 10px; color: #1a1a1a;">How long does it take to see results?</h3>
          <p style="color: #4a4a4a;">You'll see immediate results in two areas: response time (every review gets a professional response within 24 hours from day one) and review volume (our generation systems typically double or triple monthly reviews within 30 days). The compounding effects on Google ranking build over 3–6 months.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- CTA -->
    <section style="background: #1a1a1a; padding: 80px 0;">
      <div style="max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 60px 24px; text-align: center;">
        <h2 style="font-family: 'DM Serif Display', Georgia, serif; font-size: clamp(1.6rem, 3vw, 2rem); color: #fff; margin-bottom: 20px;">Your Reputation Is Already Being Written</h2>
        <p style="font-size: 1.15rem; color: #ccc; max-width: 580px; margin: 0 auto 28px;">
          The question isn't whether people are talking about your restaurant online. They are. The question is whether you're shaping the conversation or letting it shape itself.
        </p>
        <a href="/contact/" style="display: inline-block; background: #E85D04; color: #fff; padding: 16px 32px; text-decoration: none; font-weight: 600; font-size: 1.1rem; border-radius: 6px;">
          Book a Free Google Audit
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>

  </main>
</BaseLayout>
